through the elusive Kedge Robe part of your epic.<br>
<br>
Indeed they do drop from any of the darkelves in the cabin in Kith. loc (+800  +2400). A small group of friends and I, one group, had been killing the Coercer everyday for the last week or so, each time she had been wearing the blu (Ishva) robe, but going on previous posts, who also said she can drop the Kedge, we persisted. Last night we decided to clear as much of the cabin as we could.. End result, a kedge robe dropped off the Advisor.<br>
<br>
Group consisted of, 60War 59Dru 55Dru 50Clr 52Enc and 51Rog<br>
<br>
Method : Camp setup at Rivervale Zone<br>
<br>
1) War(sowed) pulls some of the camp or all, by arrow or just walking in range..takes up to 3 HT's around 800 each, then runs them to rivervale zone.and zones. (all the party expect the Rogue are a few screens away on the hill towards Highhold..so that they dont get agroed when the war zones.)<br>
<br>
2) Rogue is waiting just outside the zone in sneak/hide, and sowed. Then follows the mobs back towards their camp.(staying in bow range distance)<br>
<br>
3) War zones back into Kith (cleric heals the War, and heads back up the hill slightly with the other druids and chanter)<br>
<br>
4) As soon as War zones back in Rogue pulls (sneak still on) using a bow. (I tried a few times with daggers, but got more than one), with a bow you should have no problems if you behind them , to single one out. Most stop anyway at different times to buff themselves and there pets.<br>
<br>
5) Rogue takes small amount of dam from either HT or spell, and runs the mob back to the waiting War. Who then taunts and takes the agro straight away.<br>
<br>
6) Others come down of the hill. Chanter waits a good 10 secs (for war agro to build up), and then proceeds to (attempt) to slow the mob.  sometimes he could, sometimes he couldnt, and the fight goes from there.<br>
<br>
Notes:<br>
<br>
1) Coercer is prob the weakest mob there, in terms of HP's. And she doesnt Complete Heal. If you kill her pet she will run, when low on health..if not shes fights to death.<br>
2) None of these mobs like the use of the spell Complete heal. One of the reasons we fought at the zone was so that the cleric could CH, and then zone out and in again for another and so on. Throughout the battles, the cleric was never under 30%, even considering some of the darkies there complete heal themselves twice.<br>
3) Always be aware who IS in the zone..The last thing you want is to train a poor 8th lvl druid coming out to Kith for adventure.<br>
4) The Coercer can be taken using this method with just 4 players, 50Clr 60War 51Rog 55Dru. (we did not attempt the other darkies with this force)<br>
5) If the Coercer is wearing the Kedge(green with orange trim), she will drop it. I saw her one night last week, but before i could round up a party, she was taken down. The happy rogue sent me a tell.<br>
6) Have Dispel magic memmed. The Coercer casts a very nasty slow spell, and will often dispel most other buffs. She will always be hasted, and haste the others in the camp.<br>
7) Always tag the Coercer first...So that the hastes on the others in the camp wear off by the time you pull them. Believe me they are alot easier un-hasted.<br>
<br>
Anyway guys i hope this helps, ive read far to many post on Phinny's uncanny ability to keep hold of his robe. If you cant or dont want to clear the entire cabin, just check in when you can to see if the Coercer is wearing the Green robe..<br>
